custom ui items generated on the fly

    * items generated depend upon items specified by
      module

    * in the ladspa module, the 'plugin_name' parameter
      will determine the custom ui items generated

    * note that the 'plugin_name' parameter is not the
      triggering mechanism for the generation of custom
      ui_items.

---

what might the trigger mechanism be?

    * a special parameter? param::CUSTOM_UI_GEN. set with
      a pointer to the ui_item_list into which the custom
      items are placed?

    * a ui_item class... but how does module get item 
      list? how does sfr get it back?

    * a parameter where ui_item is flagged with          
      UI_CUSTOM_GEN but how does this differ from
      special parameter.

    * a ui_item class... with, in sfr, a dedicated
      method... to call set_param with
      param::CUSTOM_UI_GEN with a pointer to a
      ui_item_list?

    